raw_data.title: Cloud Analyst
raw_data.description: The Cloud Analyst supports the monitoring, reporting, and optimization of cloud-based systems and applications. Working under the guidance of a senior analyst or functional lead, they contribute to the analysis of system performance, cost management, and security assessments. This role involves collaborating with developers, architects, and project managers to ensure cloud operations run efficiently. As part of a broader team, the Cloud Analyst helps identify areas for improvement and supports the execution of cloud strategies aligned with business objectives.

raw_data.title: Cloud Architect
raw_data.description: The Cloud Architect designs and implements robust, scalable cloud infrastructure solutions. They lead architectural decision-making and create cloud strategies to meet organizational and project goals. This role involves managing technical teams, aligning their work with organizational goals, and ensuring smooth communication between cloud engineering, development, and client teams. The Cloud Architect also plays a critical role in mentoring junior architects and engineers, providing guidance on design patterns, deployment strategies, and optimizing cloud costs and performance.

raw_data.title: Cloud Consultant
raw_data.description: The Cloud Consultant is responsible for supporting organizations in planning, migrating, and optimizing their cloud environments, aligning solutions with business objectives and technical requirements. This role involves conducting assessments of existing infrastructure, providing recommendations for cloud services, and contributing to strategies that enhance scalability, security, and cost efficiency. Working closely with project teams and stakeholders, the Cloud Consultant assists in the implementation of best practices for cloud adoption and governance, providing practical guidance and contributing to cloud transition efforts to ensure effective, value-driven solutions.

raw_data.title: Cloud Developer
raw_data.description: The Cloud Developer is responsible for building and maintaining cloud-native applications, services, and infrastructure. They work as part of a cloud engineering team, collaborating with senior developers, architects, and project managers to ensure that development tasks align with project requirements and timelines. This role involves contributing to code development, testing, and deployment, as well as participating in team-wide code reviews and knowledge-sharing sessions to improve development practices and innovation within cloud platforms.

raw_data.title: Cloud Junior Architect
raw_data.description: The Cloud Junior Architect assists in designing cloud solutions by supporting senior architects in defining architecture frameworks, selecting cloud services, and ensuring solutions meet business and technical requirements. This role includes helping with solution diagrams, understanding architectural best practices, and participating in the assessment of new cloud technologies. The Junior Architect works on specific elements of cloud projects, contributing to design documentation, supporting implementation teams, and gaining hands-on experience in building scalable, secure, and efficient cloud environments under the mentorship of experienced architects.

raw_data.title: Cloud Project Manager
raw_data.description: The Cloud Project Manager is responsible for leading cloud-based projects from initiation through deployment. They manage cloud development teams, monitor project timelines, and coordinate with both technical and non-technical stakeholders to ensure successful project execution. This role emphasizes people management by ensuring that cloud teams are appropriately resourced, aligned with project goals, and working collaboratively to meet client requirements. The Project Manager also facilitates communication between cloud engineers, developers, and business units to ensure transparency and progress tracking.

raw_data.title: Cloud Senior Analyst
raw_data.description: The Cloud Senior Analyst provides critical insights and data analysis to support cloud-based decision-making, strategy, and performance optimization. They lead teams of analysts in assessing the efficiency, security, and costs of cloud environments. This role emphasizes team management, mentoring junior analysts, and fostering collaboration between cloud engineers, architects, and business units. The Senior Analyst is also responsible for identifying opportunities for process improvements, reducing costs, and enhancing system performance based on data-driven insights.

raw_data.title: Cloud Senior Developer
raw_data.description: The Cloud Senior Developer leads the development of cloud-native applications and platforms, managing a team of developers to ensure efficient coding practices and quality delivery. They work closely with cloud architects and functional leads to translate technical requirements into robust, scalable solutions. The Senior Developer also mentors junior developers, facilitates code reviews, and establishes development best practices. In this role, they ensure team alignment with project goals while driving innovative cloud development strategies to meet business needs.
